`request` doesn’t work well in the browser per #112 so removed it in
favor of `simple-get`

This also fixes a race condition during `npm install` that is probably
caused by some dependency’s postinstall script expecting request to be
fully installed, but it’s not because it’s hoisted to the top level
node_modules.

Call swarm.process() synchronously

We need to call swarm.process() synchronously or we'll miss events, I
think.

The initial reason I moved this code into the callback for
`githubCurrentUser` was that I wanted the `username` in order to render
the highlights. But even if we get the `username` late, `virtual-dom`
should take care of updating the DOM.

cc @maxogden @mafintosh
